10 Sequence Through Multiple Metrics

seq.df <- nest.df %>% 
  bind_cols(
    taxa_seq(.dataframe = .,
             .key_col = uid,
             .counts_col = total,
             .filter_cols_vec = c("class", "order"),
             .group_col = genus,
             .job = "rich",
             .unnest_col = data))
## Warning in instance$preRenderHook(instance): It seems your data is too big
## for client-side DataTables. You may consider server-side processing: https://

seq_mult.df <- nest.df %>% 
  bind_cols(
    taxa_seq(.dataframe = .,
             .key_col = uid,
             .counts_col = total,
             .filter_cols_vec = c("class", "order", "family"),
             .group_col = genus,
             .job = "rich",
             .unnest_col = data),
    taxa_seq(.dataframe = .,
             .key_col = uid,
             .counts_col = total,
             .filter_cols_vec = c("class", "order", "family"),
             .group_col = genus,
             .job = "pct",
             .unnest_col = data),
    taxa_seq(.dataframe = .,
             .key_col = uid,
             .counts_col = total,
             .filter_cols_vec = c("class", "order", "family"),
             .group_col = genus,
             .base_log = 2,
             .job = "shannon",
             .unnest_col = data))
